{{Infobox church |fullname = The Parish Church Of Saint Mary The Virgin |name = St Mary's |image = Uttoxeter 534277.jpg |caption = The Church seen from Bamford Bridge | pushpin map = Staffordshire | pushpin map alt = Saint Mary The Virgin | pushpin mapsize = 250 | map caption = [[Uttoxeter]] shown in [[Staffordshire]] |latd = 52.898717 | longd = -1.862825 | location = [[Uttoxeter]], [[Staffordshire]] | country = England | coordinates = {{Coord|52.898717|-1.862825|region:GB_type:landmark|display=title}} | osgridref = {{oscoor|SK093335_region:GB_scale:25000|SK 093 335}} |dedication = |denomination = [[Church of England]] |churchmanship = [[Anglican]] |diocese = [[Diocese of Lichfield]] |province = [[Province of Canterbury]] |vicar = Rev.Ted Whittaker RD |curate = |curate1 = |organistdom = |organist = |warden = |warden1 = |website = [http://uttoxeterarea.org/index.php?p=1_17_Uttoxeter-St-Mary-the-Virgin Official Website] |logo = }} '''The Parish Church Of Saint Mary The Virgin''' commonly referred to as '''St. Mary's''' by locals, is the parish church for the town of [[Uttoxeter]]. The Present structure dates from 1877 however the spire dates from the 15th century and the church is Grade II* [[Listed building|Listed]].<ref name="IoE">{{cite web|title= Parish Church Of St Mary, Bridge Street|url=http://www.imagesofengland.org.uk/Details/default.aspx?pid=2&id=272896|publisher=National Monuments record|year=2010|accessdate=30 August 2010}}</ref> This is one of two Anglican churches within the parish, the other is also St Mary's but is commonly called 'The Heath Church' to avoid confusion.
==History== Originally built in the 15th century it has been rebuilt several times since then, with the present structure dating from 1877. During the [[English Civil War]] the church was used to house royalists.{{Citation needed|date=September 2010}} By 1828 it was deemed too small so it was rebuilt then by architect [[James Trubshaw]]<ref name="LBS">{{cite web|title=Parish Church Of St Mary: LBS Number: 272896|url=http://lbonline.english-heritage.org.uk/BuildingDetailsForm.aspx?id=272896&search=y|publisher=English Heritage: Listed Buildings Online|year=2010|accessdate=30 August 2010}}{{Registration required}}</ref> and again in renovated in 1877.<ref>[http://www.achurchnearyou.com/uttoxeter-st-mary-the-virgin Church of England a Church near you St Mary the Virgin, Uttoxeter]</ref>
==Profile== The church is the main church in the Deanery of Uttoxeter and the Archdeaconry of [[Stoke-on-Trent]], after that it is in the [[Diocese of Lichfield]]. It is part of the Uttoxeter Area of parishes along with [[Bramshall]], Checkley, Gratwich, [[Kingstone, Staffordshire|Kingstone]], [[Church Leigh|Leigh]], [[St Peter's Church, Marchington|Marchington]], [[St. John's church, Marchington Woodlands|Marchington Woodlands]], [[Stramshall]] and [[Uttoxeter]] Heath Church. The current Vicar is Rev.Ted Whittaker RD who took over in 2006, recently there has been a new Sunday service informally known as the eleven o'clock designed for the younger Christian.
